# Development Workflow

## Tools and Configuration

- Node.js version is defined in [.nvmrc](mdc:.nvmrc)
- Package management uses pnpm and [pnpm-lock.yaml](mdc:pnpm-lock.yaml)
- Linting uses [eslint.config.js](mdc:eslint.config.js)
- Formatting uses [.prettierrc.json](mdc:.prettierrc.json)
- Git hooks are managed in `.husky/`
- Editor defaults are tracked in `.vscode/`

## Quality Standards

1. Run lint and format checks before finalizing changes.
2. Keep TypeScript code aligned with [tsconfig.json](mdc:tsconfig.json).
3. Use conventional commit messages when creating commits.
4. Let configured git hooks run; do not bypass them unless explicitly required.

## CI/CD

- CI pipeline definition lives in [.gitlab-ci.yml](mdc:.gitlab-ci.yml)
- Production build output is generated in `dist/`
